Ring0Glow, R0G is a software package that allows users to bypass the Valve™ Anti Cheat (VAC) software by utilizing a kernel-mode driver to evade detection in CS:GO. R0G allows users to re-create the glow functionality while in-game in order to gain an unfair advantage in-game or any other purposes.
R0G does not promote cheating in CS:GO or any game for personal or commercial gain and is simply a tool meaning the end user is responsible for all actions they commit.
R0G does not guarantee system stability while the driver is active and in some circumstances, the driver can cause blue screen errors to appear (BSOD). R0G will disable Driver Signature Enforcement® which will decrease the system security and make the user's system vulnerable to potential rootkits. R0G itself is not malicious in any way; however, certain AV's may detect it as a threat.
By continuing, you agree that you understand the risks, are fully responsible for your actions and agree to the GPL 3.0 License.
